<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1987.tb01568.x" author="Burckhardt, D" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="299 - 392" refId="B2" refString="Burckhardt, D, 1987. Jumping plant lice (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the temperate Neotropical region: Part 1. Psyllidae (subfamilies Aphalarinae, Rhinocolinae and Aphalaroidinae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 89: 299 - 392, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1987.tb01568.x" title="Jumping plant lice (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the temperate Neotropical region: Part 1. Psyllidae (subfamilies Aphalarinae, Rhinocolinae and Aphalaroidinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1987.tb01568.x" volume="89" year="1987">Burckhardt (1987)</bibRefCitation>
reported a single female from Argentina (Tucuman) suggesting that it may be introduced from North America. Whether this specimen belongs to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. ritteri" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" rank="species" species="ritteri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">A. ritteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. cannot be checked as it appears to be lost (T. Vasarhelyi, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/156853988X00241" author="Brown, RG" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Scandinavian Science Press, Leiden-New York-Kobenhavn-Koeln" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" refId="B1" refString="Brown, RG, Hodkinson, ID, 1988. Taxonomy and Ecology of the Jumping Plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). Entomonograph 9. E.J. Brill, Scandinavian Science Press, Leiden-New York-Kobenhavn-Koeln, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/156853988X00241" title="Taxonomy and Ecology of the Jumping Plant-lice of Panama (Homoptera: Psylloidea). Entomonograph 9. E. J." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/156853988X00241" year="1988">Brown and Hodkinson (1988)</bibRefCitation>
recorded a female in poor condition from Panama (Canal Zone, Herbert Osborn Collection) (USNM, slide mounted) that they questionably referred to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. curta" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">A. curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As the specimen is in poor condition, its identity cannot be determined.
</paragraph>
